This study confirmed that [$Cucumis#Plant*] is the most susceptible [$cucurbit #Plant*]genus, while [$Citrullus#Plant*] and[$ Cucurbita#Plant*] cultigens were the least susceptible genera to populations of [$P.cubensis #Virus*]in Michigan.
Area under the disease progress curve values indicated that disease progress was limited on all [$Citrullus#Plant*] cultigens compared with [$Cucumis#Plant*] cultigens, and [$pathogen#Virus*] sporulation was not detected under field conditions.
Future studies should evaluate the ability of a reduced fungicide program to control [$downy mildew#Virus*] on less susceptible [$Cucumis melo#Plant*] 'Edisto 47', 'Primo', 'Athena', 'Strike', 'Ananas', 'Banana', and 'Tam-Dew'.
Many of the [$melon cultivars#Plant*] evaluated were selected on the basis of reported resistance to [$downy mildew#Virus*], yet they showed significant disease symptoms.
It is important to evaluate candidate cultigens for resistance to local [$P.cubensis #Virus*]populations.
